# CloveJS SSE example — HTTP requests
#
# A dependency-free alternative to a Postman/Insomnia collection: this plain
# text format is read natively by JetBrains IDEs (Run > HTTP Client) and by
# VS Code's "REST Client" extension (humao.rest-client).
#
# Server-Sent Events are a streaming response, so the best way to watch a stream
# is the browser demo at http://localhost:3000/api or `curl -N` (see below).
# These blocks drive the HTTP side that feeds the streams.
#
# Start the server first: npm run dev -w clovejs-example-sse

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### Channel state over HTTP — empty until something is published
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/channels/demo

### Publish an event. Every stream open on /api/channels/demo/stream receives
### it — open http://localhost:3000/api in a browser first, then send this.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/channels/demo
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "type": "alert",
  "data": { "text": "Deploy finished" }
}

### A plain message event
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/channels/demo
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "type": "message",
  "data": { "text": "Hello from HTTP" }
}

### Channel state again — the events are in `recent` now, each with a `seq`
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/channels/demo

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Watching a stream from the terminal (run these in a shell, not the HTTP
# client). `-N` disables curl's buffering so events print as they arrive.
#
#   curl -N http://localhost:3000/api/clock
#   curl -N http://localhost:3000/api/channels/demo/stream
#
# Reconnect resume — ask for everything after event #2:
#
#   curl -N -H 'Last-Event-ID: 2' http://localhost:3000/api/channels/demo/stream
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
